ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I'd recommend it if you need it or if you're interested in the material. It's very little work -- weekly psets literally take 20 min and it's not really necessary to do the reading. You do need to put in quite a bit of time before each exam though. I was a little frustrated because I'm not sure how much meaningful material I really got out of the course -- I felt like the first half taught us "hydrogen bonds are important" and "protein structure determines function" -- but it's nothing to be scared of.
Hard course, lot of work, but rewarding even if you don't get an A.
it is a good, useful course.
